a:9:{s:7:"attribs";a:2:{s:5:"xmlns";s:36:"http://pear.php.net/dtd/rest.package";s:18:"xsi:schemaLocation";s:80:"http://pear.php.net/dtd/rest.package    http://pear.php.net/dtd/rest.package.xsd";}s:1:"n";s:31:"Netzarbeiter_CustomerActivation";s:1:"c";s:37:"connect.magentocommerce.com/community";s:2:"ca";a:2:{s:7:"attribs";a:1:{s:10:"xlink:href";s:34:"/Chiara_PEAR_Server_REST/c/Default";}s:8:"_content";s:7:"Default";}s:1:"l";s:27:"Open Software License (OSL)";s:2:"lu";s:42:"http://opensource.org/licenses/osl-3.0.php";s:1:"s";s:141:"This small extension makes it impossible for a customer to log in to magento until the account has been activated in the adminhtml interface.";s:1:"d";s:3447:"<p>This small extension makes it impossible for a customer to log in to magento, until the account has been activated in the adminhtml interface:  Customers &gt; Manage Customers &gt; (select customer) &gt; Account Information &gt; Is activated</p>
<p><strong>This extension supports Magento v1.4 and higher!</strong></p>
<p><strong></strong>It was designed to be used together with the <a href="../../../../extension/490">Netzarbeiter_LoginCatalog</a> extension. <a href="../../../../extension/490">Netzarbeiter_LoginCatalog</a> only shows products to customers that are logged in.<br />There also is the Extension <a href="../../../../extension/635">Netzarbeiter_GroupsCatalog</a> which may suit your needs better, you have to evaluate yourself what is the best solution for your case.</p>
<p>You can disable the Extension on a global or website level using the options found under System &gt; Configuration &gt; Customer &gt; Customer Activation</p>
<p>You can select email notifications for the admin (when a new customer registers) and for the customer (when her account has been activated).<br />Sample email templates in english, german and italian are provided.</p>
<p>KNOWN BUGS: - None :D</p>
<p>Changelog:<br />- Release 0.3.3:&nbsp;Use better logic to figure out the customer store id and use config value variables in sample email templates (Thanks to Ryan Price again!)<br />- Release 0.3.2:&nbsp;Added check of configuration values if emails should be sent (Thanks to Ryan Price for the patch!)<br />- Release 0.3.1:&nbsp;Added shipping and billing address models as email variables<br />- Release 0.3.0:&nbsp;Fix session logout handling for Magento 1.5 compatibility<br />- Release 0.2.9: Add japanese locale (Thanks to&nbsp;Junya Sano for the translation!)<br />- Release 0.2.8: Drop support for Magento 1.3, add customer_activated attribute to 1.4.2 (CE) customer_form_attribute table, add renderer for column to display null values as "not activated" &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp;<br />- Release 0.2.7: Enable mass activation when extension is disabled in global scope<br />- Release 0.2.6: Add italian locale it_IT, thanks to Chiara Piatti for the translation!<br />- Release 0.2.5: Magento 1.4 compatibility reease<br />- Release 0.2.4: Some refactoring and maintainance, no new features.<br />- Release 0.2.3: Make customer notification email template selectable on store view configuration scope<br />- Release 0.2.2: Added new config option to keep module active in admin customer interface, even if it is disabled in global scope<br />- Release 0.2.1: Let through API calls unchecked<br />- Release 0.2.0: New feature, send email notifications to the admin and the customer.<br />- Release 0.1.9: Include greek translation, thanks to Erik Hoeksma!<br />- Release 0.1.8: Include dutch translation, thanks to Toon van Veelen!<br />- Release 0.1.7: Show activation status in admin grid, support for mass activation (Thanks to PaulE for the code!)<br />- Release 0.1.6: declared stable<br />- Release 0.1.5beta: fixes create new customer form in the admin interface</p>
<p>With the latest release this module now also works when customer email confirmation is turned off. <br />Thanks to SeL for the french translation and the bugfixes and reports!</p>
<p>If you have ideas for improvements or find bugs, please send them to vinai at netzarbeiter.com, with Netzarbeiter_CustomerActivation as part of the subject line.</p>";s:1:"r";a:1:{s:7:"attribs";a:1:{s:10:"xlink:href";s:58:"/Chiara_PEAR_Server_REST/r/Netzarbeiter_CustomerActivation";}}}